<br>
The whole reason for these 'rules' is to limit the number of AoW's that are lost to being poofed by an unready guild.  If we took your advice, then we'd lose even more AoW's than we do now, since there is a HUGE difference between killing Statue and killing Avatar.<br>
<br>
Avatar of War is nothing like what he once was.  With 5 more levels and the gear people are sporting now, Avatar is really pretty easy, considering.  It almost always comes down to how skilled your clerics are anyway, but Statue is not even comparable to Avatar, even now.  Given enough time and attempts I could probably nail statue with little more than one group.  Avatar of war requires a full compliment of clerics and enough DPS to take him down before those clerics run out of mana.<br>
<br>
If you can kill an UNSLOWED Idol, you can kill Avatar.  In fact, Idol was always our 'warm up' mob.  We would never slow him.  <br>
<br>
And a better answer to your question...  Why should you worry about rotation rules if you aren't on the rotation?  You worry about them because someday those rotations are what will guarantee your guild's shot at a mob that some other guild wants to take from you.  Too many guilds nowadays look at the rotation rules as 'holding them back', but go look at another server sometime, and you'll see far fewer raid-capable guilds than you do on the Rathe.  Our system may seem restrictive, but without it, you'd be sucking fumes from every up-and-coming guild in the game, with no chance to ever catch up to guilds like BOTS or Tindi. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#00FFFF>- </font><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency>The Rathe Travel Agency Board</a><font color=#00FFFF> - </font><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50>General</a> <font color=#00FFFF> - </font><a href="http://www.jakefitch.com/rta/Calendar.asp">The Rathe Calendar</a><font color=#00FFFF> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.102<br>Copyright ©1999-2002 ezboard, Inc.<br>Accelerated By <a href="http://www.wbs.com/ezboard.html">JXEL</a></center></body></html>  

